<h3 align=center>Who am I?</h3>

<p> I'm a University Lecturer in this department, working on remote 
sensing 
of planetary atmospheres. Currently I am involved with the Galileo/NIMS
and Cassini/CIRS studies of the atmospheres of Jupiter, Saturn and
Titan. I am also involved with ground-based observations of the Giant 
Planets, and am using the UIST instrument on the United Kingdom InfraRed 
Telescope to monitor the changes in Uranus' cloud structure during its 
equinox (equinox in December 2007).  
<p>
When I'm not researching, I am also a Physics Tutor at <A
HREF="http://www.st-annes.ox.ac.uk/"> St Anne's College, Oxford. </A>. 
<p>

